SSE Chief Opposes Additional U.K. Nuclear Incentives, FT Reports

-- B y   J o h n   S i m p s o n
-- 
2011-06-01T00:25:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-01/sse-chief-opposes-additional-u-k-nuclear-incentives-ft-reports.html
Ian Marchant, chief executive officer
of Scottish and Southern Energy Plc, said a U.K. government
proposal that would provide incentives in addition to policies
that will give nuclear power companies a windfall is unnecessary
and could have “a negative impact on renewables,” the
Financial Times reported, citing an SSE document.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Simpson at 
 jsimpson12@bloomberg.net  